om hair loss to toe graft) to restore beauty and health. The author can be seen as a pioneer of a popular Naturopathy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aMedicine, Medieval. 0aNaturopathyvEarly works to 1800. 4aAntike Medizin. 4aNaturheilkunde. 4aPriscianus. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Medicine.  aNaturopathy.  anatural remedies.1 aBrodersen, Kai, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311069407940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311069424640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110694246423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110694246/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020